# Server Configuration - HTTPS Required

When starting or restarting the server for this project, **always use HTTPS**.

## Startup Command (default)

**Use the repo script** so the port is freed before bind (avoids WinError 10048 on Windows):

```powershell
.\scripts\start-https.ps1
```

- Runs `scripts\free-port.ps1` first, then starts uvicorn with `--reload` and SSL.
- Alternate port: `$env:CHILI_PORT='8010'; .\scripts\start-https.ps1`
- Certificates: `certs/localhost.pem`, `certs/localhost.key` (or `localhost+2.pem` / `localhost+2-key.pem` if present).

## HTTP / alternate ports

```powershell
.\scripts\start-dev.ps1
```

Picks first free port among 8000, 8010, 8020, … and runs HTTP (no SSL).

## Advanced: manual uvicorn

Only if you need custom uvicorn flags: **ensure port 8000 is free first** (otherwise you may get WinError 10048 / "Unable to connect"):

```powershell
.\scripts\free-port.ps1 -Port 8000
uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --ssl-keyfile certs/localhost.key --ssl-certfile certs/localhost.pem
```

Do **not** suggest raw uvicorn as the default; prefer `start-https.ps1`.

## Certificate Files

Located in `certs/` folder:
- `certs/localhost.pem` (certificate)
- `certs/localhost.key` (private key)

## Access URLs

- Local: `https://localhost:8000`
- LAN: `https://<LAN-IP>:8000`
